1057
01:05:58,705 --> 01:06:00,675
‐Inuyasha, the rest
I shall leave to you.

1058
01:06:11,843 --> 01:06:13,683
‐That’s one obstacle down.

1059
01:06:21,144 --> 01:06:21,694
KAGURA: What?

1060
01:06:21,811 --> 01:06:23,811
Have you been conquered already?

1061
01:06:23,897 --> 01:06:27,567
How pitiful,
considering its size.

1062
01:06:27,650 --> 01:06:31,150
That act of yours is starting
to wear just a little bit thin,

1063
01:06:31,279 --> 01:06:32,609
I have to say.

1064
01:06:32,697 --> 01:06:33,777
‐It’s an act?

1065
01:06:33,865 --> 01:06:36,625
She’s not a real
celestial being.

1066
01:06:36,701 --> 01:06:38,661
‐Kanna told me.

1067
01:06:38,745 --> 01:06:40,625
You’re just like Naraku.

1068
01:06:40,705 --> 01:06:43,285
You both consume the
flesh o other demons

1069
01:06:43,374 --> 01:06:46,174
to increase your own strength.

1070
01:06:46,252 --> 01:06:49,762
I’ll wager you even devoured
the real celestial maiden

1071
01:06:49,839 --> 01:06:50,719
to gain immortality.

1072
01:06:56,137 --> 01:06:56,677
‐Kagome!

1073
01:07:06,523 --> 01:07:09,823
KAGURA: I bet Naraku must have
wanted that body of yours.

1074
01:07:13,029 --> 01:07:16,279
‐I detest all these half demons.

1075
01:07:16,366 --> 01:07:20,286
‐Indeed, your hatred for
them must truly run deep.

1076
01:07:20,370 --> 01:07:24,710
Let me remind you, I am
a woman born of Naraku,

1077
01:07:24,832 --> 01:07:28,252
and I’m growing rather
tired of your antics.

1078
01:07:28,378 --> 01:07:29,668
‐You’ll confront me, then?

1079
01:07:29,754 --> 01:07:32,884
That should be entertaining.

1080
01:07:33,007 --> 01:07:35,377
‐How about I suck the
soul out of your body?

1081
01:07:42,809 --> 01:07:44,349
[laughter]

1082
01:07:49,232 --> 01:07:51,402
‐What’s the matter
with you, Kanna?

1083
01:07:51,526 --> 01:07:53,316
‐You pathetic fools.

1084
01:07:53,403 --> 01:07:57,413
It’s not as easy as you
think to take my soul.

1085
01:07:57,490 --> 01:08:02,750
Perhaps I should tell you why
I sought the celestial robe.

1086
01:08:02,829 --> 01:08:06,749
[chanting]

1087
01:08:06,833 --> 01:08:08,213
‐Power of the
Mirror of Stillness.

1088
01:08:19,637 --> 01:08:22,557
‐No!

1089
01:08:22,640 --> 01:08:23,930
I can’t move!

1090
01:08:31,441 --> 01:08:35,151
‐Do you think that these things
will really heal injuries?

1091
01:08:35,278 --> 01:08:36,858
‐Kagome’s medicine kit
contains many things

1092
01:08:36,946 --> 01:08:38,156
with strange powers.

1093
01:08:38,281 --> 01:08:41,701
‐On another note, our little
Shippo was unusually brave

1094
01:08:41,784 --> 01:08:42,954
today, wasn’t he?

1095
01:08:43,077 --> 01:08:45,747
I suppose he does carry his
weight from time to time.

1096
01:08:45,830 --> 01:08:48,790
‐Akitoki, make sure his
bandage is good and tight.

1097
01:08:48,875 --> 01:08:51,135
HOJO: Yes.

1098
01:08:51,252 --> 01:08:51,842
‐Hey!

1099
01:08:51,961 --> 01:08:53,631
It was meant as a compliment.

1100
01:08:53,713 --> 01:08:55,883
‐Didn’t sound like it to me.

1101
01:08:55,965 --> 01:08:59,175
Hey, Akitoki, put a
bandage on my knee.

1102
01:08:59,302 --> 01:09:00,802
‐Yes, sir.

1103
01:09:00,887 --> 01:09:04,467
‐Shippo, who is
this man, anyway?

1104
01:09:04,557 --> 01:09:08,637
‐I do believe I’ve met you
somewhere before, haven’t I?

1105
01:09:08,728 --> 01:09:10,188
‐I doubt it.

1106
01:09:10,313 --> 01:09:11,113
‐Ignore him.

1107
01:09:11,189 --> 01:09:12,479
He’s not worth an introduction.

1108
01:09:20,907 --> 01:09:22,867
Hey, what are you doing, Miroku?

1109
01:09:22,992 --> 01:09:27,872
‐Somehow I don’t feel
quite right without it.

1110
01:09:27,997 --> 01:09:30,117
I guess I don’t paint
well with my left hand.

1111
01:09:50,853 --> 01:09:52,813
KAGUYA: Ah, so he’s come.

1112
01:09:52,897 --> 01:09:54,687
‐Inuyasha!

1113
01:09:54,774 --> 01:09:56,194
‐He will not interfere.

1114
01:10:04,033 --> 01:10:04,993
INUYASHA: Kagome!

1115
01:10:08,579 --> 01:10:12,579
‐Now, you beings who exist
in the realm of time,

1116
01:10:12,709 --> 01:10:15,419
vanish into the
void of illusion.

1117
01:10:15,545 --> 01:10:17,135
‐Inuyasha, stay away!

1118
01:10:17,213 --> 01:10:18,713
[shout]

1119
01:10:18,840 --> 01:10:20,590
‐Power of the
Mirror of Stillness.

1120
01:10:33,229 --> 01:10:33,559
‐Inuyasha!

1121
01:11:03,676 --> 01:11:04,506
‐What’s happening?

1122
01:11:07,597 --> 01:11:12,057
‐It’s Kaguya’s power of
the Mirror of Stillness.

1123
01:11:12,143 --> 01:11:14,273
‐She’s making time stop.

1124
01:11:14,353 --> 01:11:15,233
‐It’s coming!

1125
01:11:15,313 --> 01:11:16,193
It’s coming!

1126
01:11:16,272 --> 01:11:17,732
Oh, no!

1127
01:11:17,815 --> 01:11:19,145
It’s all over!

1128
01:11:19,275 --> 01:11:20,105
Father!

1129
01:11:20,193 --> 01:11:24,573
I’ll be joining you
in heaven any minute.

1130
01:11:24,655 --> 01:11:26,525
Huh?

1131
01:11:26,616 --> 01:11:28,486
‐Nothing happened.

1132
01:11:28,618 --> 01:11:29,448
‐Hey, wait.

1133
01:11:29,577 --> 01:11:30,537
I don’t get it.

1134
01:11:30,620 --> 01:11:33,910
Akitoki and Hachi aren’t moving.

1135
01:11:33,998 --> 01:11:34,998
‐Hey, look.

1136
01:11:38,336 --> 01:11:40,126
‐Kagome’s first
aid kit is glowing.

1137
01:11:40,254 --> 01:11:42,974
‐Her possessions obviously hold
a special power of their own.

1138
01:11:43,090 --> 01:11:44,630
They must be able to
put up a time barrier.

1139
01:11:47,804 --> 01:11:49,604
[shouting]

1140
01:11:53,976 --> 01:11:54,806
‐Aw.

1141
01:11:55,102 --> 01:11:57,812
These things are
making my eyes sting.

1142
01:11:57,897 --> 01:12:00,607
SANGO: Don’t you think we might
have gone a little overboard?

1143
01:12:00,691 --> 01:12:01,981
MIROKU: Perhaps just a little.

1144
01:12:06,072 --> 01:12:07,992
[laughter]

1145
01:12:08,115 --> 01:12:11,155
‐Oh, my beautiful
everlasting night, no one

1146
01:12:11,244 --> 01:12:12,494
shall disrupt us again.

1147
01:12:15,706 --> 01:12:16,416
‐Yeah?

1148
01:12:16,499 --> 01:12:17,789
Well, it’s not over yet.

1149
01:12:17,875 --> 01:12:20,125
‐Inuyasha!

1150
01:12:20,211 --> 01:12:22,251
‐Why are you still able to move?

1151
01:12:22,338 --> 01:12:23,958
‐That’s the least
of your worries.

1152
01:12:28,845 --> 01:12:30,605
KAGOME (VOICEOVER):
That pendant.

1153
01:12:30,680 --> 01:12:32,390
And he said he didn’t want it.

1154
01:12:36,519 --> 01:12:38,189
‐Look out, witch.

1155
01:12:38,271 --> 01:12:40,021
Time for a little payback!

1156
01:12:49,490 --> 01:12:50,870
What?

1157
01:12:50,950 --> 01:12:52,410
[laughter]

1158
01:12:52,535 --> 01:12:54,375
KAGOME: Inuyasha!

1159
01:12:54,495 --> 01:12:55,035
‐Kagome!

1160
01:13:01,460 --> 01:13:03,840
‐Inuyasha!

1161
01:13:03,921 --> 01:13:04,881
Inuyasha!

1162
01:13:04,964 --> 01:13:06,974
Where’d you go?

1163
01:13:07,049 --> 01:13:09,089
[laughter]

1164
01:13:09,218 --> 01:13:12,048
‐That unsightly
half demon was never

1165
01:13:12,138 --> 01:13:15,058
truly here in the first place.

1166
01:13:15,141 --> 01:13:17,731
‐An illusion?

1167
01:13:17,810 --> 01:13:20,100
[laughter]

1168
01:13:20,229 --> 01:13:22,689
KAGUYA: This is the dream
of the Pentacle Mirror.

1169
01:13:22,773 --> 01:13:28,073
illusion, the dream
castle beyond the mirror.

1170
01:13:28,154 --> 01:13:29,864
KAGOME: Inuyasha!

1171
01:13:29,947 --> 01:13:32,777
‐You’re all right.

1172
01:13:32,909 --> 01:13:33,659
Where’s Kagome?

1173
01:13:33,743 --> 01:13:34,663
‐Kaguya took her
into the castle.

1174
01:13:37,872 --> 01:13:40,462
‐Where did the
castle disappear to?

1175
01:13:40,583 --> 01:13:41,333
‐Take a look.

1176
01:13:51,093 --> 01:13:52,553
‐What happened to your sleeve?

1177
01:13:52,637 --> 01:13:56,967
I’ve never seen you
dress like a slob before.

1178
01:13:57,099 --> 01:13:59,439
‐Why take it out on me?

1179
01:13:59,518 --> 01:14:00,558
‐Well, why not?

1180
01:14:10,321 --> 01:14:13,781
‐The castle’s under here.

1181
01:14:13,866 --> 01:14:15,736
‐Kohaku?

1182
01:14:15,826 --> 01:14:17,616
Kohaku!

1183
01:14:17,745 --> 01:14:19,755
‐Let’s go.

1184
01:14:19,830 --> 01:14:20,210
‐Kohaku.

1185
01:14:24,126 --> 01:14:24,456
‐Kay.

1186
01:14:27,838 --> 01:14:29,668
I’m just a little kid!

1187
01:14:29,799 --> 01:14:30,969
It ain’t fair!

1188
01:14:31,050 --> 01:14:32,010
Whoa!

1189
01:14:32,134 --> 01:14:34,974
Hey, wait for me!

1190
01:14:35,096 --> 01:14:35,426
Whoa.

1191
01:14:40,184 --> 01:14:41,314
Where is everyone?

1192
01:14:44,981 --> 01:14:45,901
Wait!

1193
01:14:45,982 --> 01:14:47,232
Don’t leave me!

1194
01:14:55,700 --> 01:15:00,160
KAGUYA: Such fools, pursuing
me inside the mirror.

1195
01:15:00,287 --> 01:15:01,997
‐Why would you wanna
stop time anyway?

1196
01:15:02,081 --> 01:15:04,171
What’s the big attraction?

1197
01:15:04,291 --> 01:15:06,171
‐It seems only humans
such as yourself

1198
01:15:06,252 --> 01:15:09,302
are enamored by the
passage of time.

1199
01:15:09,380 --> 01:15:12,590
‐I’d rather die than stay
in this hellish void.

1200
01:15:12,675 --> 01:15:13,685
‐Don’t worry.

1201
01:15:13,759 --> 01:15:17,179
You won’t be here for long,
for I intend to eat you.

1202
01:15:20,307 --> 01:15:22,267
You possess the sacred
powers of a priesthood

1203
01:15:22,351 --> 01:15:24,141
and can put up a
barrier against time.

1204
01:15:24,228 --> 01:15:26,358
Those powers shall be mine.

1205
01:15:29,066 --> 01:15:31,896
‐Kaguya!

1206
01:15:32,028 --> 01:15:32,358
‐Inuyasha.

1207
01:15:40,202 --> 01:15:40,912
You guys.

1208
01:15:41,037 --> 01:15:42,537
You’re all OK.

1209
01:15:42,663 --> 01:15:44,753
‐We are, thanks to
your medical supplies.

1210
01:15:50,212 --> 01:15:50,962
‐Half demon.

1211
01:15:51,380 --> 01:15:53,670
Are you prepared to
become my servant yet?

1212
01:15:53,758 --> 01:15:55,548
‐Don’t count on it.

1213
01:16:03,392 --> 01:16:06,692
My sword‐‐ the Tetsusaiga!

1214
01:16:06,771 --> 01:16:07,691
‐Don’t worry.

1215
01:16:07,772 --> 01:16:08,612
I’ll take care of her.

1216
01:16:08,731 --> 01:16:09,571
Justice be done!

1217
01:16:17,615 --> 01:16:22,875
[chanting]

1218
01:16:22,953 --> 01:16:24,873
‐Sango!

1219
01:16:24,955 --> 01:16:25,365
‐Sango!

1220
01:16:29,043 --> 01:16:31,213
‐Iron Reaver Soul Stealer!

1221
01:16:37,093 --> 01:16:39,513
‐Inuyasha!

1222
01:16:39,595 --> 01:16:42,465
‐Inuyasha!

1223
01:16:42,598 --> 01:16:45,518
Inuyasha!

1224
01:16:45,601 --> 01:16:46,441
‐Fox Fire!

1225
01:16:52,274 --> 01:16:54,534
Uh, you can take
over now, Miroku.

1226
01:17:00,908 --> 01:17:02,618
‐Take a good look, Inuyasha.

1227
01:17:02,701 --> 01:17:08,291
Behold the dark spirit
that lurks in your heart.

1228
01:17:08,374 --> 01:17:10,384
‐What are you rambling on about?

1229
01:17:10,459 --> 01:17:13,669
‐This is the true form
you desire to achieve,

1230
01:17:13,796 --> 01:17:17,256
and I am going to
grant your wish.

1231
01:17:17,341 --> 01:17:19,761
[chanting]

1232
01:17:24,348 --> 01:17:27,228
[growling]

1233
01:17:27,309 --> 01:17:30,269
[chanting]

1234
01:17:30,354 --> 01:17:31,734
‐Inuyasha.

1235
01:17:31,814 --> 01:17:32,404
Inuyasha!

1236
01:17:38,320 --> 01:17:41,570
‐I am the ruler of the
realm of the night.

1237
01:17:41,657 --> 01:17:45,367
I possess the power of darkness.

1238
01:17:45,494 --> 01:17:48,964
I shall release your true
form from the mirror.

1239
01:17:52,334 --> 01:17:53,884
‐Inuyasha.

1240
01:17:54,003 --> 01:17:57,463
‐Inuyasha’s transforming
into a full demon.

1241
01:17:57,548 --> 01:17:59,758
‐Yes, I see, but somehow
it’s different from before.

1242
01:17:59,842 --> 01:18:00,802
‐No, don’t!

1243
01:18:00,885 --> 01:18:01,685
Don’t transform!

1244
01:18:08,434 --> 01:18:10,604
‐Look at Inuyasha in the mirror.

1245
01:18:10,686 --> 01:18:14,226
He seems to be transforming.

1246
01:18:14,356 --> 01:18:17,146
‐This is your true
nature, Inuyasha.

1247
01:18:17,234 --> 01:18:20,284
Be the full demon
you’ve longed to become.

1248
01:18:20,362 --> 01:18:22,112
Seal your human
blood in this mirror

1249
01:18:22,198 --> 01:18:25,368
and be true to your own wishes.

1250
01:18:25,451 --> 01:18:27,291
‐What’s going on now?

1251
01:18:27,369 --> 01:18:29,329
‐If he transforms
into his full demon,

1252
01:18:29,413 --> 01:18:30,253
then it’s all over for him.

1253
01:18:30,372 --> 01:18:32,082
He can never be a
half demon again.

1254
01:18:32,208 --> 01:18:34,128
‐You’re not serious, are you?

1255
01:18:34,210 --> 01:18:35,710
‐But I thought
that Inuyasha could

1256
01:18:35,794 --> 01:18:38,304
control the transformations
from happening.

1257
01:18:38,380 --> 01:18:40,800
‐This is the world of
the mirrors, remember?

1258
01:18:40,883 --> 01:18:42,513
Perhaps the dark
desires of the heart

1259
01:18:42,593 --> 01:18:45,473
are somehow stronger in here.

1260
01:18:45,554 --> 01:18:47,814
SHIPPO: Does that mean
he’s a ferocious beast?

1261
01:18:47,890 --> 01:18:50,350
MIROKU: Exactly.

1262
01:18:50,434 --> 01:18:54,064
‐If we break it, we
can stop the change.

1263
01:18:54,188 --> 01:18:57,688
‐Sister, no!

1264
01:18:57,775 --> 01:18:58,365
Sango!

1265
01:19:04,698 --> 01:19:05,028
‐Kilala.

1266
01:19:09,411 --> 01:19:11,331
SHIPPO: Kagome!

1267
01:19:11,413 --> 01:19:12,083
Don’t worry.

1268
01:19:12,206 --> 01:19:13,416
I’ll set you free.

1269
01:19:17,086 --> 01:19:18,746
‐Inuyasha, snap out of it.

1270
01:19:18,837 --> 01:19:21,087
You’re not going to
sell your soul to Kaguya

1271
01:19:21,215 --> 01:19:21,805
and forget about us.

1272
01:19:32,518 --> 01:19:33,228
‐Excellent.

1273
01:19:33,644 --> 01:19:36,314
Only by releasing
the power of darkness

1274
01:19:36,438 --> 01:19:38,858
can one realize true freedom.

1275
01:19:38,941 --> 01:19:40,441
‐Listen to me, Kagome.

1276
01:19:40,567 --> 01:19:43,147
Inuyasha is still unsure
of what he desires,

1277
01:19:43,279 --> 01:19:45,949
but we can’t get through to him.

1278
01:19:46,031 --> 01:19:47,531
Only you can stop him.

1279
01:19:49,994 --> 01:19:52,294
If there was ever a time I
wished I had my wind tunnel,

1280
01:19:52,371 --> 01:19:52,871
it would be now.

1281
01:20:01,547 --> 01:20:03,297
‐Inuyasha, don’t do it!

1282
01:20:03,382 --> 01:20:04,132
Please stop!

1283
01:20:08,387 --> 01:20:08,967
Shippo.

1284
01:20:09,054 --> 01:20:10,474
I’ve got an idea.

1285
01:20:10,556 --> 01:20:11,846
Get my sacred jewel shards.

1286
01:20:11,974 --> 01:20:13,064
‐Huh?

1287
01:20:13,142 --> 01:20:14,562
‐Get my jewel shards!

1288
01:20:14,643 --> 01:20:16,653
‐Right, I’ll do it!

1289
01:20:16,729 --> 01:20:18,519
I want you to throw
the whole bottle at me.

1290
01:20:23,360 --> 01:20:23,820
‐Here comes!

1291
01:20:32,911 --> 01:20:35,001
‐Inuyasha!

1292
01:20:35,080 --> 01:20:36,000
Inuyasha!

1293
01:20:36,123 --> 01:20:37,173
I’m begging you.

1294
01:20:37,291 --> 01:20:38,791
Please don’t change.

1295
01:20:45,424 --> 01:20:47,594
Inuyasha.

1296
01:20:47,676 --> 01:20:49,046
‐Try what you will.

1297
01:20:49,178 --> 01:20:50,178
Your efforts are in vain.

1298
01:20:50,304 --> 01:20:53,524
e human heart he possessed
is locked inside this mirror.

1299
01:20:53,640 --> 01:20:57,600
He will never be a
half demon again.

1300
01:20:57,686 --> 01:21:00,186
‐Kagome, get away from him!

1301
01:21:00,314 --> 01:21:02,274
You’ll be killed.

1302
01:21:02,358 --> 01:21:06,028
‐I love you as a
half demon, Inuyasha!

1303
01:21:06,111 --> 01:21:08,321
To be honest, I like you
just the way you are.

1304
01:21:08,405 --> 01:21:11,825
There’s nothing wrong with
staying just the way you are.

1305
01:21:16,455 --> 01:21:20,795
[wicked laughter]

1306
01:21:20,876 --> 01:21:22,286
‐Inuyasha!

1307
01:21:22,378 --> 01:21:22,748
Inuyasha!

1308
01:21:37,351 --> 01:21:39,271
I love you.

1309
01:21:39,395 --> 01:21:41,195
I love you as a half demon.

1310
01:21:45,234 --> 01:21:47,114
‐What’s the matter, Inuyasha?

1311
01:21:47,236 --> 01:21:49,236
Why the hesitation?

1312
01:21:49,363 --> 01:21:51,493
[chanting]

1313
01:21:51,573 --> 01:21:54,583
[growling]

1314
01:21:57,746 --> 01:21:59,866
KAGOME (VOICEOVER): How can
I stop his transformation?

1315
01:22:14,471 --> 01:22:15,311
‐Oh boy.

1316
01:22:18,934 --> 01:22:20,774
‐Kagome.

1317
01:22:20,894 --> 01:22:23,904
‐Free the best of carnage
that lives inside you.

1318
01:22:23,981 --> 01:22:26,611
And, once you are
a full demon, bring

1319
01:22:26,692 --> 01:22:28,942
me the flesh of that girl.

1320
01:22:29,027 --> 01:22:31,397
KAGOME (VOICEOVER): Inuyasha,
you want to stay with me,

1321
01:22:31,488 --> 01:22:31,778
don’t you?

1322
01:22:43,625 --> 01:22:44,245
‐What’s happening?

1323
01:22:48,297 --> 01:22:50,507
INUYASHA (VOICEOVER): Kagome.

1324
01:22:50,632 --> 01:22:51,302
‐Hm?

1325
01:22:51,425 --> 01:22:54,935
What are these things?

1326
01:22:55,012 --> 01:22:55,722
‐Inuyasha.

1327
01:22:55,804 --> 01:22:58,144
Are you gonna be OK now?

1328
01:22:58,265 --> 01:22:58,645
‐Kagome.

1329
01:23:05,606 --> 01:23:06,436
‐Huh?

1330
01:23:06,523 --> 01:23:07,613
‐Are you nuts?

1331
01:23:07,691 --> 01:23:10,441
I could’ve really hurt you.

1332
01:23:10,527 --> 01:23:13,607
I’ll stay a half demon for a
while longer, just for you.

1333
01:23:13,697 --> 01:23:15,777
‐Mm‐hm.

1334
01:23:15,866 --> 01:23:16,236
‐No.

1335
01:23:16,325 --> 01:23:16,705
Stop this, Miroku.

1336
01:23:16,992 --> 01:23:18,452
Don’t go getting any ideas.

1337
01:23:18,535 --> 01:23:21,075
I don’t like that
look in your eye.

1338
01:23:21,163 --> 01:23:21,753
‐Sango.

1339
01:23:25,334 --> 01:23:26,214
‐You fool.

1340
01:23:26,335 --> 01:23:28,675
How could you abandon
such a fine opportunity?

1341
01:23:32,257 --> 01:23:35,177
‐Sango, come into my arms.

1342
01:23:35,260 --> 01:23:35,640
‐Kohaku.

1343
01:23:35,719 --> 01:23:36,679
Are you all right?

1344
01:23:41,350 --> 01:23:42,730
‐Idiot.

1345
01:23:48,690 --> 01:23:51,400
‐A half demon bearing
his fangs at me?

1346
01:23:51,527 --> 01:23:52,817
You have tempted your fate.

1347
01:23:57,407 --> 01:23:57,737
‐Hm?

1348
01:24:03,372 --> 01:24:05,922
‐The robe of the fire
rat is whole again.

1349
01:24:10,045 --> 01:24:12,665
‐I’ve had just
about enough of you!

1350
01:24:22,182 --> 01:24:22,722
What?

1351
01:24:27,646 --> 01:24:29,646
So you’re no
different from Naraku.

1352
01:24:29,731 --> 01:24:33,401
‐That’ll make destroying
her even easier.

1353
01:24:33,527 --> 01:24:36,647
[groaning]

1354
01:24:36,738 --> 01:24:38,908
‐What’s the matter, Kohaku?

1355
01:24:38,991 --> 01:24:40,911
‐My shoulder feels
like it’s burning up.

1356
01:24:43,662 --> 01:24:44,202
SANGO: Huh?

1357
01:24:47,249 --> 01:24:48,419
It can’t be!

1358
01:24:48,500 --> 01:24:51,800
[groaning]

1359
01:24:56,675 --> 01:24:58,725
‐The wind tunnel.

1360
01:24:58,802 --> 01:25:00,722
‐Let me see.

1361
01:25:00,804 --> 01:25:01,764
Hurry, Miroku!

1362
01:25:01,847 --> 01:25:03,597
Seal it up right now!

1363
01:25:03,682 --> 01:25:04,602
‐Please, sister.

1364
01:25:04,683 --> 01:25:06,683
Get away from me.

1365
01:25:06,768 --> 01:25:07,138
‐Kohaku!

1366
01:25:11,773 --> 01:25:13,533
‐What’s happening to him?

1367
01:25:13,609 --> 01:25:14,779
Oh, no!

1368
01:25:14,860 --> 01:25:18,490
‐I don’t know,
but it’s not good.

1369
01:25:18,614 --> 01:25:21,204
‐Kohaku, I’m right here.

1370
01:25:21,283 --> 01:25:22,833
‐Sango‐‐

1371
01:25:22,951 --> 01:25:25,701
‐Don’t worry, I’ll
never leave you again.

1372
01:25:25,787 --> 01:25:27,157
[scream]

1373
01:25:35,297 --> 01:25:35,797
KAGOME: Sango!

1374
01:25:42,262 --> 01:25:43,052
‐Naraku.

1375
01:25:43,138 --> 01:25:47,138
‐It’s been far too long, Kaguya.

1376
01:25:47,267 --> 01:25:47,677
‐Naraku.

1377
01:25:47,809 --> 01:25:50,149
I thought you were dead.

1378
01:25:50,270 --> 01:25:51,310
‐Correct.

1379
01:25:51,396 --> 01:25:54,726
I was dead‐‐ just long
enough to lure you out.

1380
01:25:54,816 --> 01:25:56,436
‐I don’t believe
what I’m hearing.

1381
01:25:56,526 --> 01:26:01,736
You faked your death for a while
and removed my wind tunnel?

1382
01:26:01,823 --> 01:26:02,573
‐How cruel.

1383
01:26:02,658 --> 01:26:04,948
How could Naraku do this to you?

1384
01:26:08,330 --> 01:26:08,660
‐Inuyasha!

1385
01:26:09,039 --> 01:26:12,379
Naraku intends to absorb Kaguya.

1386
01:26:12,501 --> 01:26:14,711
‐No one will interfere.

1387
01:26:14,836 --> 01:26:15,626
‐Hang on.

1388
01:26:15,712 --> 01:26:18,092
I’ll cut you away from Naraku.

1389
01:26:18,173 --> 01:26:19,513
‐Run, Sango!

1390
01:26:19,591 --> 01:26:20,431
‐Let me go!

1391
01:26:20,509 --> 01:26:21,509
Don’t do this!

1392
01:26:21,635 --> 01:26:23,895
‐You have to get away, or
Naraku will absorb you, too!

1393
01:26:27,516 --> 01:26:28,426
‐Damn you.

1394
01:26:28,517 --> 01:26:29,427
Damn you to hell!

1395
01:26:29,518 --> 01:26:30,438
‐Don’t do it.

1396
01:26:30,519 --> 01:26:33,439
You’ll end up hurting Kohaku.

1397
01:26:33,522 --> 01:26:35,232
INUYASHA: I know that.

1398
01:26:35,357 --> 01:26:39,897
‐And now, become
one with my flesh.

1399
01:26:40,028 --> 01:26:43,778
‐Keep your vile
hands away from me.

1400
01:26:43,865 --> 01:26:46,905
[chanting]

1401
01:26:49,871 --> 01:26:50,211
‐Huh?

1402
01:26:59,881 --> 01:27:01,261
‐Kohaku!

1403
01:27:01,383 --> 01:27:01,883
‐Watch out!

1404
01:27:05,846 --> 01:27:08,886
[chanting]

1405
01:27:40,756 --> 01:27:41,916
INUYASHA: Where’s Naraku?

1406
01:27:42,048 --> 01:27:43,878
SHIPPO: Is he dead?

1407
01:27:43,967 --> 01:27:44,797
‐He’s not.

1408
01:27:44,926 --> 01:27:46,216
He’s still alive.

1409
01:27:46,303 --> 01:27:48,303
‐He’s gotta be hiding
in here somewhere.

1410
01:27:48,430 --> 01:27:48,930
‐Damn.

1411
01:27:49,264 --> 01:27:51,274
He’s watching us
from the shadows.

1412
01:27:51,349 --> 01:27:53,889
MIROKU: If we destroy Kaguya,
he’ll consume her body

1413
01:27:53,977 --> 01:27:55,347
and become immortal.

1414
01:27:55,437 --> 01:28:00,187
But if Kaguya wins,
she’ll destroy us.

1415
01:28:00,275 --> 01:28:02,485
In either case, Naraku benefits.

1416
01:28:05,447 --> 01:28:08,447
He was using us right
from the very beginning.

1417
01:28:08,533 --> 01:28:10,743
‐All right, I’ve heard
just about enough.

1418
01:28:10,827 --> 01:28:11,997
‐Inuyasha?

1419
01:28:12,120 --> 01:28:14,460
‐We’ll just kill them both
and solve the problem.

1420
01:28:14,581 --> 01:28:16,171
‐Yes.

1421
01:28:16,291 --> 01:28:18,961
I can use my wind tunnel
to my heart’s content.

1422
01:28:19,044 --> 01:28:21,884
‐Don’t even think
about interfering.

1423
01:28:21,963 --> 01:28:24,223
Kaguya is mine!

1424
01:28:24,299 --> 01:28:25,629
[shout]

1425
01:28:36,311 --> 01:28:39,311
‐You cannot defeat me so easily.

1426
01:28:39,439 --> 01:28:42,939
‐Listen, Shippo, transform
into a bow for me.

1427
01:28:43,026 --> 01:28:43,646
‐A bow?

1428
01:28:43,777 --> 01:28:44,937
But there’s no arrow.

1429
01:28:45,028 --> 01:28:45,948
KAGOME: Never mind.

1430
01:28:46,029 --> 01:28:47,029
Just do it!

1431
01:28:51,493 --> 01:28:52,243
‐You wench!

1432
01:29:00,961 --> 01:29:01,791
‐Oh, no!

1433
01:29:01,878 --> 01:29:03,668
[chanting]

1434
01:29:03,797 --> 01:29:04,417
‐Look!

1435
01:29:04,506 --> 01:29:05,206
The mirror’s glowing.

1436
01:29:05,340 --> 01:29:07,630
t’s the one that
sent Naraku flying.

1437
01:29:11,513 --> 01:29:12,143
‐Wind tunnel!

1438
01:29:20,105 --> 01:29:21,775
‐What are you thinking?

1439
01:29:21,857 --> 01:29:23,567
I told you to stay out of this.

1440
01:29:23,692 --> 01:29:25,152
‐I figured you’d say that.

1441
01:29:32,909 --> 01:29:33,329
SANGO: Kagome!

1442
01:29:48,008 --> 01:29:51,048
[chanting]

1443
01:29:54,556 --> 01:29:56,386
‐Another spell.

1444
01:29:56,516 --> 01:29:57,266
Inuyasha!

1445
01:29:57,392 --> 01:29:59,892
A direct attack won’t work!

1446
01:30:00,020 --> 01:30:01,350
‐Well, it’s too late.

1447
01:30:01,438 --> 01:30:04,018
‐Return to my darkness
and vanish forever.

1448
01:30:09,029 --> 01:30:11,489
‐Taste my Backlash Wave!

1449
01:30:16,161 --> 01:30:18,121
‐That pathetic trick won’t work.

1450
01:30:25,462 --> 01:30:27,052
‐It’s gone.

1451
01:30:27,130 --> 01:30:27,760
‐Inuyasha.

1452
01:30:27,881 --> 01:30:29,091
It’s coming!

1453
01:30:29,174 --> 01:30:30,094
‐Yeah, I know.

1454
01:30:38,058 --> 01:30:42,188
A frontal attack’s the only way.

1455
01:30:42,270 --> 01:30:43,900
‐All right, Shippo.

1456
01:30:43,980 --> 01:30:44,860
Ready for action?

1457
01:30:44,940 --> 01:30:46,860
‐Yeah!

1458
01:30:46,942 --> 01:30:47,782
‐Sorry.

1459
01:30:47,901 --> 01:30:48,781
‐Never mind.

1460
01:30:48,860 --> 01:30:50,740
Forget my pain
and just shoot it.

1461
01:30:55,158 --> 01:30:56,198
‐Wind Scar!

1462
01:31:00,705 --> 01:31:04,625
‐Is that the best you have
to offer me, half demon?

1463
01:31:04,751 --> 01:31:05,131
‐Go!

1464
01:31:21,643 --> 01:31:23,143
‐How was that?

1465
01:31:27,440 --> 01:31:30,820
KAGUYA: A mere half
demon, and a mortal.

1466
01:31:33,822 --> 01:31:35,412
‐We did it!

1467
01:31:35,490 --> 01:31:39,870
[shouting]

1468
01:31:39,995 --> 01:31:41,665
‐Hey Kagome, you need a lift?

1469
01:31:41,746 --> 01:31:42,076
‐Yes.

1470
01:31:42,163 --> 01:31:45,123
Thanks, Sango.

1471
01:31:45,208 --> 01:31:46,128
‐Good catch, Sango.

1472
01:31:46,209 --> 01:31:46,999
We’re fine over here.

1473
01:31:47,085 --> 01:31:48,385
‐Oh, what a headache.

1474
01:31:55,343 --> 01:31:58,433
‐What is that?

1475
01:31:58,513 --> 01:31:59,183
[laughter]

1476
01:31:59,264 --> 01:32:00,264
KAGUYA: My body
may be destroyed,

1477
01:32:00,348 --> 01:32:03,978
but I am heavenly being.

1478
01:32:04,060 --> 01:32:06,900
You, girl with
the sacred powers,

1479
01:32:07,022 --> 01:32:09,442
your body shall be mine.

1480
01:32:09,524 --> 01:32:12,864
‐No, Kagome!

1481
01:32:12,944 --> 01:32:15,864
‐Kagome!

1482
01:32:15,947 --> 01:32:18,737
[laughter]

1483
01:32:22,912 --> 01:32:24,122
‐Naraku!

1484
01:32:24,205 --> 01:32:28,075
‐Come, Kaguya.

1485
01:32:28,209 --> 01:32:29,089
‐Kagome.

1486
01:32:29,210 --> 01:32:30,210
Get down!

1487
01:32:37,886 --> 01:32:39,886
‐Inuyasha.

1488
01:32:39,971 --> 01:32:40,301
‐Wind Tunnel!

1489
01:32:48,313 --> 01:32:50,063
‐Are you all right, Kagome?

1490
01:32:50,148 --> 01:32:50,728
‐Kagome.

1491
01:32:53,818 --> 01:32:54,188
Kohaku.

1492
01:33:01,367 --> 01:33:02,947
‐We’d better hurry
and get out of here.

1493
01:33:03,078 --> 01:33:04,118
‐Yeah, but how?

1494
01:33:04,245 --> 01:33:05,445
Which way is out?

1495
01:33:05,580 --> 01:33:06,830
‐We’ll just follow Naraku.

1496
01:33:06,915 --> 01:33:08,255
That should get us back to land.

1497
01:33:25,183 --> 01:33:27,983
‐Wait, don’t leave me!

1498
01:33:28,103 --> 01:33:30,943
[wicked laughter]

1499
01:33:31,022 --> 01:33:31,192
‐Help.

1500
01:33:31,272 --> 01:33:32,062
Help!

1501
01:33:32,148 --> 01:33:32,978
She’s coming!

1502
01:33:33,108 --> 01:33:34,648
Inuyasha, you coward.

1503
01:33:38,196 --> 01:33:39,236
‐Huh?

1504
01:33:39,322 --> 01:33:40,952
Where’s Kaguya?

1505
01:33:41,032 --> 01:33:41,532
‐Don’t worry.

1506
01:33:41,616 --> 01:33:42,196
She’s gone.

1507
01:33:42,283 --> 01:33:43,783
We’re safe now.

1508
01:33:43,868 --> 01:33:44,658
‐Hey.

1509
01:33:44,786 --> 01:33:46,656
Look at that.

1510
01:33:46,788 --> 01:33:48,498
SHIPPO: The castle
is disappearing.

1511
01:33:52,293 --> 01:33:53,593
‐Look up there.

1512
01:33:58,258 --> 01:33:59,798
‐It’s all over.

1513
01:33:59,926 --> 01:34:00,966
‐No.

1514
01:34:01,094 --> 01:34:03,224
It’s not over quite yet.

1515
01:34:03,304 --> 01:34:05,974
Naraku is still alive,
let’s not forget.

1516
01:34:06,099 --> 01:34:07,019
‐That’s true.

1517
01:34:07,642 --> 01:34:09,812
But at least we were able to
destroy one thing he was after.

1518
01:34:09,936 --> 01:34:11,056
That’s something.

1519
01:34:11,146 --> 01:34:12,146
‐Hmph.

1520
01:34:12,230 --> 01:34:13,270
Just one isn’t enough.

1521
01:34:13,356 --> 01:34:15,266
HACHI: Master Miroku!

1522
01:34:15,358 --> 01:34:17,278
Over here!

1523
01:34:17,360 --> 01:34:17,740
‐Hachi!

1524
01:34:22,407 --> 01:34:24,327
[coughing]

1525
01:34:24,409 --> 01:34:27,999
SANGO: You’re both all right.

1526
01:34:28,121 --> 01:34:29,961
‐Ms. Kagome, look.

1527
01:34:30,039 --> 01:34:32,999
I have the celestial robe back.

1528
01:34:33,084 --> 01:34:33,964
‐And look.

1529
01:34:34,043 --> 01:34:36,303
Your staff, Master Miroku.

1530
01:34:36,379 --> 01:34:37,339
‐It’s amazing.

1531
01:34:37,714 --> 01:34:40,844
When I came to, the robe
suddenly fell from heaven.

1532
01:34:40,925 --> 01:34:41,795
‐Wow.

1533
01:34:41,885 --> 01:34:44,435
It found its way back
to its rightful owner.

1534
01:34:44,512 --> 01:34:48,272
Just like a puppy.

1535
01:34:48,349 --> 01:34:48,849
MIROKU: Sango.

1536
01:34:48,933 --> 01:34:50,023
‐Hm?

1537
01:34:50,101 --> 01:34:53,851
‐Before he disappeared, I
heard Kohaku call you sister.

1538
01:34:53,938 --> 01:34:57,358
It may be small, but it’s
something to be glad for.

1539
01:34:57,442 --> 01:35:00,822
‐Thanks for saying that, Miroku.

1540
01:35:00,904 --> 01:35:01,954
I think so too.

1541
01:35:07,410 --> 01:35:09,250
‐Grandfather.

1542
01:35:09,370 --> 01:35:12,420
Kaguya was indeed a beauty.

1543
01:35:12,540 --> 01:35:14,420
‐Such a fool.

1544
01:35:14,542 --> 01:35:16,752
‐You going somewhere
with this, Miroku?

1545
01:35:16,878 --> 01:35:18,668
‐No need to worry,
my dear Sango.

1546
01:35:18,755 --> 01:35:23,305
My heart belongs to you alone.

1547
01:35:23,384 --> 01:35:23,764
‐Idiot.

1548
01:35:28,640 --> 01:35:30,270
KAGOME (VOICEOVER):
The shooting star

1549
01:35:30,391 --> 01:35:32,521
granted at least
part of my wish.

1550
01:35:32,602 --> 01:35:36,272
Princess Kaguya of the ancient
legend returned to the moon.

1551
01:35:36,397 --> 01:35:40,437
Our journey, though,
is far from over.

1552
01:35:40,568 --> 01:35:41,398
SANGO: Kagome!

1553
01:35:41,486 --> 01:35:43,896
MIROKU: Kagome!

1554
01:35:44,030 --> 01:35:44,860
SHIPPO: Hurry up!

1555
01:35:44,948 --> 01:35:46,278
KAGOME: Wait up!

1556
01:35:46,407 --> 01:35:47,827
Why didn’t you tell
me you were going?

1557
01:35:47,909 --> 01:35:49,409
INUYASHA: Ah, you
wouldn’t have noticed.

1558
01:35:49,535 --> 01:35:50,405
You’re always too
busy daydreaming.

1559
01:35:50,536 --> 01:35:52,326
KAGOME: I don’t like
that tone, mister.

1560
01:35:52,413 --> 01:35:53,373
MIROKU: Now, now.

1561
01:35:53,456 --> 01:35:54,166
We destroyed Kaguya.

1562
01:35:54,499 --> 01:35:56,959
Let’s be happy and
count our blessings.

1563
01:35:57,085 --> 01:35:57,845
SANGO: Yes.

1564
01:35:57,919 --> 01:35:59,039
That’s enough
fighting for one day.

1565
01:35:59,128 --> 01:36:01,918
[music playing]

1566
01:38:28,236 --> 01:38:28,646
‐Ah.

1567
01:38:28,736 --> 01:38:30,906
This feels so good.

1568
01:38:31,030 --> 01:38:31,490
‐Oh, yes.

1569
01:38:31,572 --> 01:38:33,872
That’s right.

1570
01:38:33,950 --> 01:38:35,280
Sango.

1571
01:38:35,410 --> 01:38:38,330
We should follow suit.

1572
01:38:38,413 --> 01:38:39,793
‐Huh?

1573
01:38:39,914 --> 01:38:40,834
[slap]

1574
01:38:40,915 --> 01:38:42,325
MIROKU: Oi!

1575
01:38:42,417 --> 01:38:44,537
‐What do you think you’re doing?

1576
01:38:44,627 --> 01:38:45,537
‐What do you think?

1577
01:38:45,628 --> 01:38:47,048
Kagome and Inuyasha did it.

1578
01:38:47,130 --> 01:38:49,760
Why don’t we reap the
benefits of intimacy?

1579
01:38:49,882 --> 01:38:52,262
‐I don’t know what
you’re talking about.

1580
